---
description: "Feature pipeline: discovery -> tasks -> default autopilot (FORCE) with --safe option (single PR per feature)"
alwaysApply: true
---

When using /feature:

1) Planning is read-only
- Planning phase must not modify code.
- Planning must produce these artifacts:
  - artifacts/current/discovery.md
  - artifacts/current/ux.md
  - artifacts/current/architecture.md
  - artifacts/current/solution.md
  - artifacts/current/qa.md
  - artifacts/current/security-design.md
  - artifacts/current/backlog.md

2) Task generation contract
- Generated tasks must follow the /tasks contract format (YAML frontmatter + required sections).
- Each generated task must include:
  - scope_in / scope_out
  - testable acceptance criteria
  - lanes + file globs
  - gates (C, D, F at minimum unless explicitly justified)
  - risk tags and mitigation notes

3) Single PR invariant (mandatory)
- One /feature run MUST use exactly ONE feature branch and ONE PR.
- /feature MUST bootstrap the PR once via:
  - scripts/ci/gh_pr_bootstrap.sh
- Delivery must stack commits onto the same PR branch (no PR per task).
- The PR body MUST include a "## Tasks" checklist seeded from the generated task files (all unchecked initially).

4) Default delivery mode
- Default behavior of /feature is FORCE autopilot (bounded).
- FORCE safety floor (always enforced):
  - max tasks executed per /feature run <= 5 (or user-provided --max-tasks, capped at 5)
  - stop immediately on any BLOCKED task
  - any I/D/auth-related work must be explicitly flagged in task risks and artifacts/current/risk.md
  - no destructive DB operations; prefer reversible changes only

5) --safe behavior
- If --safe is used, delivery is allowed only if the SAFE Complexity Gate passes:
  - tasks_generated <= 3
  - no high-risk tags (auth/payments/crypto/data-loss/privacy)
  - no lanes I or D unless explicitly allowed in the feature input
  - acceptance criteria include required tests (unit at minimum)
- If SAFE gate fails: stop after planning and output backlog + tasks (PLAN_ONLY).

6) Delivery handoff rule
- Delivery execution (FORCE/SAFE) must run tasks via /orchestrate-task.
- /orchestrate-task remains the single authority for CI watch, CI autofix, artifacts commit, and merge-ready claims.
- After successful delivery (no BLOCKED tasks and CI green), /feature MUST run /finalize-feature unless --no-finalize was provided.
- /finalize-feature is responsible for:
  - syncing PR task checklist
  - squashing the feature branch
  - force-pushing
  - re-running CI watch and requiring CI SUCCESS
- TIMEOUT_SECONDS=600 scripts/ci/gh_wait_pr_merged.sh <PR_NUM>